title: For Sale/Trade:  SRM 1216 with extras BNIB
postcontent:
Gen 2 model brand new in box. SRM 1216 semi-auto 12 gauge. Comes with 4 16rd magazines. No shipping, will meet State line /Cheyenne since I live in Greeley CO. 2,800$ and you won't find one cheaper with this many mags. Would accept a Glock 19 Gen 4 as partial trade plus 2,100$ (if the Glock is new). Keltec PMR, Springfield pistols, Hk pistols, limited edition pistols, Dan Wesson 1911's Or a Kel-Tec KSG.  Here is some info on the gun. Please let me know what you have and guns only when offering a trade!  



SRM Arms Model 1216 shotgun is operated using delayed blowback principle, which is rather unusual for shotguns. It employs roller-delayed action with two-part bolt and two rollers in its head, which enter recesses in the barrel extension. This action is very similar to that found in many older weapons by Heckler & Koch (such as G3 or MP5) based on WW2-era German Stg.45(M) design.Model 1216 shotgun is built using bullpup layout, with polymer housing / stock and steel upper receiver, connected by cross-pins. Ejection ports are located on either side of the receiver, with one which is not in use being closed by removable ejection port cover. Normally Model 1216 shotgun is set up to eject to the right, although user can disassemble the gun and set it for left-side ejection, if required. One of most unusual features of the SRM Arms Model 1216 shotgun is its feed system. It employs detachable rotary magazine with four channels, each containing its own spring and follower. Each channel can hold up to four rounds in the same manner as any common tubular shotgun magazine. When magazine is inserted into the gun, it is located below the barrel. To feed the weapon, magazine should be rotated until one of its compartments is in topmost (12’o clock) position and aligned with feed port in the gun. Once it is done, cartridge retainer in the topmost compartment is disengaged, and first cartridge is pushed rearwards from magazine and onto the lifter platform in the gun. Once all four cartridges from topmost magazine are expended, bolt hold-open device engages the bolt in its rearward (open) position, indicating that magazine compartment is empty. After that, user shall push the indexing lever(s) at the front of the magazine, and manually rotate it 90 degrees to either side, until next full compartment is aligned with the feed port. Once it is done, fresh round is automatically fed from magazine and bolt hold-open device is released, chambering the round and making gun ready for the next shot. Once all four compartments are empty (or firing is done), rotary magazine cam be removed from the gun by pushing magazine release button, located in front of the magazine, below the muzzle. Empty or partially loaded magazines can be topped up only when removed from the gun.Other features of the SRM Arms Model 1216 shotgun include conveniently located manual safety, which can be set on left or on right side of the gun, and set of integral Picatinny type rails, which can be used to install variety of sighting devices (Red Dot or iron sights), as well as laser aiming modules and/or tactical flashlights.

title: For Sale/Trade:  WTS/WTT M1A w/ Troy MCS FDE, FDE Magpul Accessories, Upgrades, Case, Ammo, Etc.
postcontent:
http://postimg.org/image/kj6zfp9k7/
http://postimg.org/image/6bhar1wvb/

I am looking to sell (possibly trade - see below) my Springfield M1A Socom 16. To hopefully prevent any further issues, I am not looking to part this out, but I will under the right circumstances which I will list below.
This rifle has many accessories, upgrades, etc and I will only be considering reasonable offers. Please do your research on the gun/parts/acc/upgrades/etc before making an offer. I am more than happy to answer any questions.

This is a Socom 16 made in 2007-8. I am unsure of the exact month/year but that is what the previous owner told me and my research shows that to be a close timeframe for this rifle's production. According to the previous owner, I am now the third owner of this rifle. According to how many rounds the previous owner shot through it and what (supposedly) the original owner put through it along with how many times I've shot it I'd say its had right about 4-500 rounds through it. The rifle itself is not in perfect condition, it has the normal rubmarks of a used M1A, however it is completely rust-free, has no glaring marks other than the normal wear marks, and has a very nice and shiny barrel. With the exception of the internal upgrades I've added this rifle, which I'll explain shortly, is all SAI parts other than the trigger group which is a GI HRA that probably originally came with the rifle. 

As you can see from the pictures, the rifle has been heavily modified with accessories and parts, however it can be completely returned to the original configuration it was in when I received it which is as such: A stock Socom 16 (w/ HRA TG) in a GI walnut stock with a GI fiberglass handguard (scout mount not attached but included). The previous owner sold off the original synthetic black stock and put it into a GI walnut and removed the scout mount, which I still have. There is nothing wrong with the rifle/parts, I'm just looking for something else right now. 

Here is a complete build list/part list of what I am offering if someone wants all of this stuff:

1. SAI Socom 16 
2. GI Walnut Stock w/ GI cleaning kit in stock and M14 tool
3. GI Fiberglass Handguard
4. GI Fiberglass Handguard cut out to allow for the scout mount attachment
5. All original parts that were carefully removed to install upgrades/Troy chassis/etc, i.e. rear sight, handguard clip, forward handguard retainer, original SAI socom brake, guide rod, piston, gas plug, etc. 
6. Troy MCS Chassis in FDE, originally purchased as a bare chassis
7. Magpul UBR Stock in FDE
8. Limbsaver - Magpul Precision Fit Buttpad - including the original Magpul Buttpad as well
9. Magpul MOE+ grip in FDE
10. Troy Micro sight set in FDE - not tritium
11. Rail ladders - not sure of manufacturer
12. Magpul XTM Enhanced Rail Covers in FDE/BLK
13. Gear Sector QD Sling Mount in FDE
14. Precision Muzzle Device Alignment Washers - originally purchased from Brownells
15. SAI 20rd magazine
16. 3x 20rd magazines from Thermold
17. Troy Claymore Muzzle Brake
18. Folding Mech that can be used in conjunction with stock/chassis to make the rifle have a side folding stock
19. AR Receiver End Plate - not needed for the UBR stock due to design but suggested for most others
20. 308 Tromix Shark Brake
21. Sadlak Cleaning Drill Set (3 drills)
22. Sadlak Gas Cylinder Wrench - Aluminum
23. 30 cal Boresnake
24. Grease - White Lithium and Shooters Choice
25. Blue Loctite
26. Magpul AFG2 in FDE
27. Vltor Modpod in FDE
28. Buffer Tech Recoil Buffer
29. Wolff Extra Power Recoil Spring
30. Sadlak NM Guide Rod
31. Smith Enterprise Chrome Piston
32. Smith Enterprise Socom Gas Plug
33. Pelican 1720 Rifle Case
34. Sadlak Extended Magazine Release
35. Smith Enterprise Extended Bolt Catch/Release

I also have 40 rounds of Winchester 7.62x51mm 147gr FMJ, 160 rounds of Hirtenberger 7.62x51, and 300 rounds of Radway Green in Bandoliers/Ammo Can

There is well over $4000 invested into the stuff listed above. If someone wants a very nice, upgraded, and accessorized M1A with all that stuff I just listed then awesome! If not let me know what you're interested in and we can probably work something out. There are a few stipulations however.
1. The point of this is to sell the rifle and hopefully most of the stuff listed or work out a trade, if I have to part out the stuff after selling the rifle then fine but the goal is to sell the rifle. 
2. The ammo will not be sold/traded until/unless the rifle is sold/traded.
3. If you don't want/are not interested in the Troy MCS or other upgrades/accessories then I can put the gun back into whatever configuration up to current and all the way back to how I received it.
4. I know what the stuff is worth/selling for, please do not lowball me or contact me unless a serious potential buyer or have a trade I'm looking for. 

Here is the ONE AND ONLY TRADE I am looking for: An FNH PS90 in Black or OD - doesn't matter, but must be in excellent, working condition. Trade offers can be supplemented with ammo, mags, accessories, optics, other guns, etc. but this rifle must be part of the trade if a trade is to occur. I am willing to adjust the list above to offer something fair in trade, but I will not be considering trading a used PS90 with one mag and original box for the entire list above - sorry.

Other Things I will consider in addition to the PS90, other than what I already listed in general:
1. Concealed Carry Guns - pocket carry potential preferably
2. 1911s 
3. Shotguns - Pump preferable
4. Anything reasonable, definitely gun related

I know this is a long listing, but I'd like to have most questions answered before they need asked so I'm trying to be as thorough as possible.

I am looking to get $3500 out of everything listed above, without the ammo. I will do $3700 with the ammo. Obviously due to the size/weight of some of these items I would prefer to sell/trade FTF in Central Ohio (preferably close to Columbus), but if you'd like to pay for shipping then I have no hesitation to ship it to your FFL, but the cost of shipping will be covered by the buyer - I can provide an estimate if desired, if the final cost of the shipment goes over my initial estimate for shipping then I will cover the difference. I will consider shipped trades over state borders on a case-by-case basis. 

Thanks for looking! Please either send me an email at REDACTED, message me on arfcom (slowest), or call/text me at REDACTED (fastest). I am located in Westerville, OH.

title: For Sale/Trade:   Case of Federal Auto Match 22LR (prefer to trade)
postcontent:
Quite a while back, I ordered and only recently received 2 cases of Federal Auto Match. ONLY ONE is for sale/trade. I am keeping the other one for my Ruger 10/22 which eats this stuff like candy. This ammo is terrific for semi-auto rifles and pistols. It's 40 grain bullet and clean burning powder cycle them great without gumming up the action. 
 However, I do most of my shooting with a pair of bolt action 22s that actually prefer the cheaper 36 grain copper plated Federal Champion and Remington Golden bullets.
 I'll sell the whole case for $400.00, but would rather trade it for Federal Champion 36 grain copper plated 22LR, or I'd even consider trading for Remington Golden Bullets 22LR. That way I won't have to spend the next 6-8 months trying to replace it.
 If you want a good 22LR cartridge that will cycle your semi-auto properly without gumming it up, this is it! Make a trade or buy it outright. (trades preferred)
 Acceptable trades would be: one box of FEDERAL AUTO MATCH for one box Federal Champion. Or, one box of auto match for one 525 round box of Remington Golden bullets 22LR
